OL,6,F"Any normal parent would never take
OL,7,Fthat risk. I will never understand it,
OL,8,FI will never forgive it," Mr Ellis
OL,9,Finsisted.
OL,11,FKatherine Robinson, mitigating, said
OL,12,FSheppard had suffered from a severe
OL,13,Fmental health condition as a result of
OL,14,Fthe trauma of the incident.
OL,16,F"(It) will stay with her forever," Ms
OL,17,FRobinson said.
OL,19,FJudge House said the case was "an
OL,20,Fabsolute tragedy".
